The paper presents a tool for discovering porting bugs in performance-critical code, which involves a bounded model checking method that reduces portability analysis to the satisfiability modulo theories (SMT) problem with integer difference logic. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL), Architecture (cs.AR), Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Software Engineering (cs.SE), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
